{
    "analysis": "We have loaded and summarized all telemetry files. metric.csv (321,411 rows) spans timestamps from 1647784800 to 1647788400, which covers the incident window. trace.csv and log.csv both start at 1647786600 and end at 1647788400, and error_logs.csv contains 4 rows for frontend-1 within the incident period. The metric data contains many container/node KPIs (notably many container.node-6 metrics) and the trace data contains many front-end-originated traces (trace.from_frontend-*). Next we should run metric-based anomaly detection (using global thresholds) to narrow down candidate component-KPI faults inside the incident window before analyzing traces and logs. ",
